HEADWORD: Refrangible
<hw>Re*fran"gi*ble</hw> <pr>(-fr?n"j?*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧frangible</ets>. See <er>Refract</er>.]</ety>
<def>Capable of being refracted, or turned out of a direct course, in
passing from one medium to another, as rays of light.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Re*fran"gi*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

